<br>
If you want a severe mana drain for your pet buff, make it a Mana DoT. Your pet lives and does more damage, it saps more of your strength to keep it capable of doing that. Once you run out of mana, the buff fades.<br>
<br>
Frankly, the pet BETTER be hitting those stats on EVERY mob to make it worthwhile to use, including Luclin, for the downsides you listed. Heck, the refresh delay ALONE is all that stops Melee from reusing their disciplines more often, and those disciplines are quite potent. If ours hurts/drains us, it better be godly. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
